{"id":"270460cc-b6b3-4c2d-971c-27870bb589d0","title":"1550/12/20: To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"563b8dca-7bde-47b6-81c5-11307f2e34a6","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, December 20th, 1550.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"6178d126-616d-4e16-88b5-a4e01749a80c","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"85b1bd28-1fd1-44ed-b37c-8adaa93b1825","type":"codex/time-reference","start":11,"end":29,"value":"88b60c9f-750b-4d79-a462-87693ce465d4","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d14e6b76-79b5-46b2-86e3-fd7660c9d711","type":"style/superscript","start":22,"end":23,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"d70fe962-02df-4a81-a7d6-b9e78c68bea0","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"64d4e88d-6191-442f-bc5f-82de49f5539b","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"4ad64ac3-5fae-44d6-adf0-18d57559a373","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"1d4f09ae-02aa-41e7-97e4-08aab5641362","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"1cfccb94-d5b7-4501-8201-783c35c2fceb","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"b0b77e6a-f489-4f7b-8ba8-5fecb3e96160","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0I have received the marzolini, there were twelve cheeses in all. They are most excellent and I shall give some to my friends and keep the remainder for the house. But as I have said to thee on former occasions, thou art to send me nothing more unless I ask for it; especially send nothing that costs thee money.\u00A0As to thy getting married, which is a necessary\u00A0step, I have nothing to say, unless it be that thou must not consider the dowry; for that is an index rather of worldly possessions than of character. Thou must seek only for nobility and for soundness of body: and thou must seek for personal goodness rather than anything else. As to beauty, as thou art not thyself the most handsome youth in Florence, it\u00A0skills not for thee to trouble overmuch about it, provided that she be neither deformed nor diseased. I\u00A0have nothing to add on this head.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"bcd825fa-03b9-4ae5-90be-70279988d630","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":7,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"73763e07-d92f-40ea-92cd-a73dd6d9adeb","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"cb4ca286-a768-4b89-93c1-1170ad167431","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":12,"end":12,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7e652cc0-fb75-4266-9b75-8350c6ddc4eb","type":"style/italics","start":32,"end":40,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"845ec4b2-117d-434a-b885-cdd874ee712b","type":"language","start":32,"end":40,"value":"it","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"ab7856a7-9fde-4498-935e-f95784de2910","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":32,"end":40,"value":"03c4670a-7e7e-4402-a6ce-e59df0e2e08e","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"471dde06-594b-4264-a601-a17bd0fbfa36","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":72,"end":74,"value":"03c4670a-7e7e-4402-a6ce-e59df0e2e08e","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"58428afe-0f81-4b99-a8fe-bfb4c4ea086e","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":77,"end":80,"value":"03c4670a-7e7e-4402-a6ce-e59df0e2e08e","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"45eac3f2-45b9-4e8f-b0c9-2a2bbca3afa0","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":105,"end":105,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-